Networking Scenarios -

11. App not accessible from internet

Checks:

Public subnet
Route table → 0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
Internet Gateway attached
Public IP assigned
Security group
12. Works internally but not externally

Causes:

No public IP
No IGW
SG blocking external traffic
13. Works from one subnet, not another

Checks:

Route table difference
NACL rules
Subnet association
14. Security Group vs NACL
Feature	Security Group	NACL
Type	Stateful	Stateless
Level	Instance	Subnet
Return traffic	Auto allowed	Must allow

👉 Rule:

Response blocked → NACL issue
Inbound blocked → SG issue
15. DNS not resolving

Checks:

VPC DNS enabled
Route53 records
Domain config
16. High network latency

Causes:

Cross-AZ/region traffic
Network congestion

Fix:

Use same AZ
Check metrics
17. VPC peering not working

Checks:

Route tables on both sides
No CIDR overlap
SG allows traffic
18. Private subnet cannot access internet

Checks:

NAT Gateway present
Route table → 0.0.0.0/0 → NAT
19. Route table misconfiguration

Checks:

Correct routes
Subnet association
Proper next hop
20. Packet loss / intermittent connectivity

Causes:

Network congestion
NACL blocking
High CPU/network

Tools:

CloudWatch
traceroute
🎯 Key Interview Lines
“I debug layer by layer from IGW to application”
“Security group is stateful, NACL is stateless”
“VPC peering needs routing on both sides”
“Private subnet requires NAT for internet access”
